SERVER SIDE CONFIGURATION:
------------------------------

Step 1: Configure Sendmail:
==============================
Edit-->/etc/mail/sendmail.mc and following:

define(`SMART_HOST', `email-smtp.us-east-1.amazonaws.com')dnl
define(`RELAY_MAILER_ARGS', `TCP $h 587')dnl
define(`ESMTP_MAILER_ARGS', `TCP $h 587')dnl
FEATURE(`authinfo', `hash -o /etc/mail/authinfo.db')dnl

MASQUERADE_AS(`mparellak8s.xyz')dnl
FEATURE(masquerade_envelope)dnl
FEATURE(masquerade_entire_domain)dnl
FEATURE(genericstable)dnl
GENERICS_DOMAIN_FILE(`/etc/mail/generics-domains')dnl

MAILER(smtp)dnl
MAILER(procmail)dnl


Step 2: Create supporting files:
=================================
Edit -/etc/mail/generics-domains  and must have following

client1.1.local
localhost
localhost.localdomain

Open --> /etc/mail/genericstable and below line
root    noreply@mparellak8s.xyz

run -> makemap hash /etc/mail/genericstable < /etc/mail/genericstable


Step 3: Authinfo for SES:
============================

Create /etc/mail/authinfo -> and add below

AuthInfo:email-smtp.us-east-1.amazonaws.com "U:root" "I:YOUR_SES_SMTP_USERNAME" "P:YOUR_SES_SMTP_PASSWORD" "M:PLAIN"

and run following commands:
makemap hash /etc/mail/authinfo < /etc/mail/authinfo
chmod 600 /etc/mail/authinfo /etc/mail/authinfo.db

Step 4: Rebuild and restart.

cd /etc/mail
make
systemctl restart sendmail


Step 5: Test:
================
sendmail -f noreply@mparellak8s.xyz -v maheshparella243@gmail.com <<EOF
Subject: SES Test
From: noreply@mparellak8s.xyz

Hello Mahesh, SES test mail.
EOF








